  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\n\r\nPeople might apply memory and CPU limits to the containers. CPU limitation is not an issue, but memory is different.\r\nSome of the Ceph daemons manage their memory cache (OSD and MDS), so their memory consumption grows over time. This might lead to OOM kill issues on Pod if the ceph-{osd,mds} process consume more memory.\r\nWe will end up with a cascading effect where daemons keep flapping.\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\n\r\nThe idea would be to tune several ceph options (`osd_memory_target` and `mds_cache_memory_limit`) so that when the container starts the ceph process will be configured appropriately and will never go above the limit applied to the container (if any).\r\n",
